Decision: I choose Brainwashed because its low compression, subtle dynamics, intimate lead vocals, warm analog midrange, restrained electric guitar and cohesive sequencing best preserve vocal immediacy and reward uninterrupted listening — the core of what I look for. I reject A Decade of Hits despite its nice packaging and liner notes because its compilation nature and guitar/solo‑driven blues‑rock focus conflict with my dislike of multi‑era anthologies and my preference for consistent, vocal‑forward, sparsely arranged albums.

